manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Optimised for Static Pressure During the development of the new P8, special emphasis was placed on a focused airstream and thus a high static pressure. The fan ensures extremely efficient cooling, even with increased air resistance. Therefore, the P8 is particularly suitable for use on heatsinks and radiators. High Quality Bearing Thanks to an alloy/lubricant combination developed in Germany, friction within the bearing is reduced and greater efficiency is achieved. As a result, there is less heat development as well as less bearing noise, which means you can enjoy a longer service life from your fan. Two Way Installation Push warm air out of the case, pull cool air into the case. Highly Efficient The ARCTIC P8 Case Fan is the ultimate PC-Cooler solution.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Quiet and seem to work well.
reviews.reviewText: I purchased these for an 18-year-old CoolerMaster Praetorian case that has four 80mm fans. The fans seem to need replacing every 5 years or so. There are a lot of really good fans available, but if I had to pay $60 to $70 for fans, I'd put the money into a new case with modern features.I don't know anything about the Arctic brand, but these fans work as good as the previous fans I had which were Enermax Marathon. These fans are quiet and I've had no issues with overheating, I game on this system and it has an i9-12900K and Arc A770. If the fans last 5 years, they'll outlast the useful life of this system.The "PWM sharing" feature is just marketing for a built-in Y-connector that lets you daisy-chain fans together. It did allow me to remove a separate Y-connector from my PC, so I guess it was useful.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 6, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very easy, very quiet, very happy.
reviews.reviewText: I'm resurrecting an Oooold 98SE machine, and noticed that it could use some extra cooling power. Saw these fans at 5 for under $20 and I couldn't pass it up. Great deal. 2 fans went in without a hitch, secured easily and are very quiet. My power source fan is the only thing I hear as it's about twice the size. Sound wise, it's as if I never installed them at all. They seem like they push a respectable amount of air. Just what this old machine needed. Now as soon as I get the OS re-installed, it joins my XP, WIN 8 and Ubuntu machines in the guinea pig server so I can practice attacking it. CEH style that is. (Just need to set up a virtual server now with 2008 in there.) Excellent deal, as long as they hold up. I would recommend them. The only very minor issue is that others said that they came with rubber bumpers to keep them even quieter. I didn't get any bumpers, but they mounted up tightly and there is no danger of rattling etc. Satisfied, so far. Time will tell but 5 stars for now. If it changes, I'll let y'all know.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 23, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The stock fan that came in a power amp sounded like a jet engine running. It was very loud. The Arctic P8 moves the same amount of air and is barely noticeable. I, once again, have a quiet place to work without the distraction of a noisy fan. I would recommend this product for anyone looking for a good, quiet fan.

reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars This little thing pushes air!
reviews.reviewText: Grabbed this mini arctic to use as a Ram fan and man is it strong and very quiet! Have tried several mini fans and non come close to the level of quiet this guy has at full rpm. The single only downside is that it’s not pwm so adjusting rpm isn’t an option but even at full 3000 rpm it’s extremely quiet!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 29, 2015
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Silent and powerful!
reviews.reviewText: These fans are untouchable for the price!Yes, there are 80mm that push more air, but they cannot do so as quietly as these run.I used these to replace a set of 4 Raidmax green led fans in my gaming PC. I was using my old case, opticals, and PSU to build a new PC, and decided to replace all of the fans during the build as a couple were no longer running properly. I used four of these and a 120mm Artic fan in the front of the case.I wired the 120 and 2 of the 80's to the motherboard. These fans do not come with 4-pin connectors and I had no adapters on hand, so I had to splice to 4-pin connectors to connect directly to the PSU.When I finally powered up the new machine, I freaked out thinking none of the fans were running. I'm accustomed to being able to hear the constant hum of 5 fans all the time, yet i could hear nothing. I ran my hand beside and behind the case and sure enough, just as much air being pushed as my noisy $20ea Raidmax fans used to push.I'm a bit saddened to lose the cool factor of my glowing led fans, but these do the job just as well and much more quietly.

reviews.reviewTitle: Una ventola per Pc di ottima affidabilità e qualità
reviews.reviewText: Ho acquistato questa ventola nel 2017 e tutt'ora nel 2022 e ancora operativa e non sta dando il minimo problema, nessuna scocciatura, nessun rumore fastidioso.E una ventola veramente affidabile, di ottima fattura e silenziosità, infatti ne ho acquistate altre, anche di misure differenti.Ne consiglio l'acquisto, Se cercate una ventola per Pc, affidabile e duratura, puntate tranquillamente a quelle della ARCTIC.

reviews.reviewTitle: Auch wenn Amazon davorgeschaltet ist lohnt eine Mail an den Arctic Support...
reviews.reviewText: Amazon wollte wegen Mangel an einem kleinen Teil der Lieferung alles Austauschen (5er pack gekauft) doch ich hatte keinen Ersatz in der Größe und schon alles verbaut(IPX) jedenfalls hab ich gezögert, einen neuen Tab geöffnet und Arctic einfach angeschrieben und den Mangel geschildert statt alles wieder auszubauen. Eine Stunde später befand sich Ersatz auf dem Postweg. Hut ab. 5* (Danke "Carsten")

reviews.reviewTitle: ARCTIC F8 Pro TC => Ben oltre le aspettative
reviews.reviewText: Comprata per sostituire una ventola rumorosa, usata per anni.Non avevo mai preso una ventola con il sensore, visto il prezzo ho deciso di provarla.RISULTATO eccezionale sotto tutti i punti di vista, silenziosissima al minimo e comunque con una buona buona portata d'aria. Un pochino più rumorosa quando gira 2000rpm, ma si "confonde" con la ventola della CPU e della scheda video.Super consigliata!
